page.title: 17Morris Dancing Club
page.content: I go to St. Andrews{Morris Dancing} Club which is held in the Social Club in Higher Road, Halewood. We meet on Tuesdays between 5 p.m. and 7 p.m. My friends Paula Huxley and Paula Morrison go with me.{Membership} details are dealt with by Pat Hart and Jackie Elliott, the trainers. It costs 30p. We have competitions every Saturday and have been to Wales, Manchester, St. Helens and Runcorn. We sometimes put on{displays}at the Fairways Leisure Centre. We usually travel by bus to the various places. I have 5{medals}and the troupe itself has lots of{awards.} I like the trainers and the people that go there. LISA ELLIOTT (9)
